00069 {
00070     Squeue *queue;
00071 
00072     /* Alloc queue and initialize it */
00073     queue = (Squeue *) L_alloc (Squeue_pool);
00074 
00075     sprintf (queue->name, "%s %d", name, id);
00076     queue->size = 0;
00077     queue->current = NULL;

00081     return (queue);

00127 /*
00128  * Adds a sinfo to the end of the queue
00129  */
00130 void L_enqueue (Squeue *queue, Sched_Info *sinfo)
00131 {
00132     Sq_entry *entry;
00133 
00134     /* Alloc entry */
00135     entry = (Sq_entry *) L_alloc (Sq_entry_pool);
00136 
00137     /* Initialize fields */
00138     entry->queue = queue;
00139     entry->sinfo = sinfo;
00140 
00141     /* Add entry to sinfo's entry list */
00142     entry->prev_queue = NULL;
00143     entry->next_queue = sinfo->entry_list;
00144     if (sinfo->entry_list != NULL)
00145         sinfo->entry_list->prev_queue = entry;
00146     sinfo->entry_list = entry;
00147 
00148     /* Add entry to end of queue's entry list */
00149     if (queue->tail == NULL)
00150         queue->head = entry;
00151     else
00152         queue->tail->next_entry = entry;
00153     entry->prev_entry = queue->tail;
00154     entry->next_entry = NULL;
00155     queue->tail = entry;
00156 
00157     /* Increment queue size */
00158     queue->size++;
00159 }

00161 void L_dequeue (Squeue *queue, Sched_Info *sinfo)
00162 {
00163     Sq_entry *entry;
00164 
00165     for (entry=queue->head; entry!=NULL; entry=entry->next_entry)
00166     {
00167         if (entry->sinfo == sinfo)
00168         {
00169             if (queue->current == entry)
00170             {
00171                 queue->current = entry->prev_entry;
00172                 if (queue->current == NULL)
00173                     L_reset_queue_current(queue);
00174             }
00175 
00176             /* Remove entry from current queue */
00177             if (entry->prev_entry == NULL)
00178                 queue->head = entry->next_entry;
00179             else
00180                 entry->prev_entry->next_entry = entry->next_entry;
00181         
00182             if (entry->next_entry == NULL)
00183                 queue->tail = entry->prev_entry;
00184             else
00185                 entry->next_entry->prev_entry = entry->prev_entry;
00186         
00187             /* Decrement queue size */
00188             queue->size--;
00189         
00190             /* Remove entry from sinfo's entry list */
00191             if (entry->prev_queue == NULL)
00192                 entry->sinfo->entry_list = entry->next_queue;
00193             else
00194                 entry->prev_queue->next_queue = entry->next_queue;
00195         
00196             if (entry->next_queue != NULL)
00197                 entry->next_queue->prev_queue = entry->prev_queue;
00198         
00199             /* Free entry memory */
00200             L_free (Sq_entry_pool, entry);
00201 
00202             break;
00203         }
00204     }
00205 }
00206 /*
00207  * Only use this routine when you are completely finished with the
00208  * queue entry!  The queue entry will be freed and some of its information
00209  * will be corrupted.
00210  */
00211 void L_dequeue_entry (Sq_entry *entry)
00212 {
00213     Squeue *queue;
00214 
00215     queue = entry->queue;
00216 
00217     if (queue->current == entry)
00218     {
00219         queue->current = entry->prev_entry;
00220         if (queue->current == NULL)
00221             L_reset_queue_current(queue);
00222     }
00223 
00224     /* Remove entry from current queue */
00225     if (entry->prev_entry == NULL)
00226         queue->head = entry->next_entry;
00227     else
00228         entry->prev_entry->next_entry = entry->next_entry;
00229 
00230     if (entry->next_entry == NULL)
00231         queue->tail = entry->prev_entry;
00232     else
00233         entry->next_entry->prev_entry = entry->prev_entry;
00234 
00235     /* Decrement queue size */
00236     queue->size--;
00237 
00238     /* Remove entry from sinfo's entry list */
00239     if (entry->prev_queue == NULL)
00240         entry->sinfo->entry_list = entry->next_queue;
00241     else
00242         entry->prev_queue->next_queue = entry->next_queue;
00243 
00244     if (entry->next_queue != NULL)
00245         entry->next_queue->prev_queue = entry->prev_queue;
00246 
00247     /* Free entry memory */
00248     L_free (Sq_entry_pool, entry);
00249 }

00251 /*
00252  * Only use this routine when you are completely finished with all queue
00253  * entries associated with the sinfo!  The queue entries will be freed and
00254  * some of their information will be corrupted.
00255  */
00256 void L_dequeue_from_all (Sched_Info *sinfo)
00257 {
00258     Sq_entry *entry, *next_queue;
00259 
00260     for (entry = sinfo->entry_list; entry != NULL; entry = next_queue)
00261     {
00262         next_queue = entry->next_queue;
00263         L_dequeue_entry (entry);
00264     }

00267 /*
00268  * Enqueue the sinfo before the specified entry in the queue(before).
00269  * 
00270  * A NULL pointer will cause the sinfo to be enqueued at the end of the queue.
00271  */
00272 void L_enqueue_before (Squeue *queue, Sched_Info *sinfo, Sq_entry *before)
00273 {
00274     Sq_entry *entry;
00275 
00276     /* Alloc entry */
00277     entry = (Sq_entry *) L_alloc (Sq_entry_pool);
00278 
00279     /* Initialize fields */
00280     entry->queue = queue;
00281     entry->sinfo = sinfo;
00282 
00283     /* Add entry to sinfo's entry list */
00284     entry->prev_queue = NULL;
00285     entry->next_queue = sinfo->entry_list;
00286     if (sinfo->entry_list != NULL)
00287         sinfo->entry_list->prev_queue = entry;
00288     sinfo->entry_list = entry;
00289 
00290     /* if before NULL, add entry to end of queue's entry list */
00291     if (before == NULL)
00292     {
00293         if (queue->tail == NULL)
00294             queue->head = entry;
00295         else
00296             queue->tail->next_entry = entry;
00297         entry->prev_entry = queue->tail;
00298         entry->next_entry = NULL;
00299         queue->tail = entry;
00300     }
00301 
00302     /* Otherwise add before 'before' */
00303     else
00304     {
00305         if (before->prev_entry == NULL)
00306             queue->head = entry;
00307         else
00308             before->prev_entry->next_entry = entry;
00309         entry->prev_entry = before->prev_entry;
00310         entry->next_entry = before;
00311         before->prev_entry = entry;
00312     }
00313 
00314     /* Increment queue size */
00315     queue->size++;
00316 }

00318 /*
00319  * Moves the entry before the specified entry (before) in the new_queue.
00320  * This is more efficient than dequeueing and enqueueing the sinfo.
00321  *
00322  * A NULL pointer for 'before' causes the entry to be appended to the end
00323  * of the queue.
00324  */
00325 void L_move_entry_before (Squeue *new_queue, Sq_entry *entry, Sq_entry *before)
00326 {
00327     Squeue *old_queue;
00328 
00329     /* Remove entry from current queue */
00330     old_queue = entry->queue;
00331     if (entry->prev_entry == NULL)
00332         old_queue->head = entry->next_entry;
00333     else
00334         entry->prev_entry = entry->next_entry;
00335 
00336     if (entry->next_entry == NULL)
00337         old_queue->tail = entry->prev_entry;
00338     else
00339         entry->next_entry->prev_entry = entry->prev_entry;
00340 
00341     /* Decrease old queue's size */
00342     old_queue->size--;
00343 
00344     /* Change entry to current queue */
00345     entry->queue = new_queue;
00346 
00347     /* if before NULL, add entry to end of queue's entry list */
00348     if (before == NULL)
00349     {
00350         if (new_queue->tail == NULL)
00351             new_queue->head = entry;
00352         else
00353             new_queue->tail->next_entry = entry;
00354         entry->prev_entry = new_queue->tail;
00355         entry->next_entry = NULL;
00356         new_queue->tail = entry;
00357     }
00358 
00359     /* Otherwise add before 'before' */
00360     else
00361     {
00362         if (before->prev_entry == NULL)
00363             new_queue->head = entry;
00364         else
00365             before->prev_entry->next_entry = entry;
00366         entry->prev_entry = before->prev_entry;
00367         entry->next_entry = before;
00368         before->prev_entry = entry;
00369     }
00370 
00371     /* Increment new queues size */
00372     new_queue->size++;
00373 }

00376 void L_enqueue_min_to_max_1 (Squeue *queue, Sched_Info *sinfo, float key)
00377 {
00378     int         found, passed_current = 0;
00379     float       current_key;
00380     Sq_entry    *current;
00381 
00382     sinfo->sort_key1 = key;
00383 
00384     if (queue->tail == NULL)
00385     {   /* empty queue */
00386         L_enqueue (queue, sinfo);
00387     }
00388     else
00389     {
00390         /* non-empty queue */
00391         current = queue->head;
00392         if (queue->current == (Sq_entry *) -1) passed_current = 1;
00393 
00394         /* Search for appropriate location in queue */
00395         found = 0;
00396         while ((current) && (!found))
00397         {
00398             current_key = current->sinfo->sort_key1;
00399 
00400             if (key < current_key)
00401             {
00402                 L_enqueue_before ( queue, sinfo, current);
00403                 if (!passed_current) queue->current = current->prev_entry;
00404                 found = 1;
00405             }
00406             else
00407             {
00408                 if (current == queue->current) passed_current = 1;
00409 
00410                 current = current->next_entry;
00411             }
00412         }
00413 
00414         if (!found)
00415         { /* Append to end of list */
00416             L_enqueue (queue, sinfo);
00417         }
00418     }
00419 }
